<!--
# Behavior Tree - Sequence Control Flow

A `<Sequence>` runs its children in order, threading the input through each and
stopping at the first failure. Each child here is a `<Log::Message>` leaf; both
pass, so the sequence passes. `{RunOnLoad}` runs the root on load, then exits.

    beet --main=examples/action/behavior_tree.bsx
-->
<Sequence {RunOnLoad}>
	<Log::Message("running child1")/>
	<Log::Message("running child2")/>
</Sequence>
